<span id="freeTextContainer5945465940433655492">This is the second book of Richard Bach which I read after Jonathan Livingston Seagull .<br/>Richard has a flawless art of story telling. It engages the reader so well that reader itself feels as it&apos;s his own life-story being narrated. The eye towards details , capturing of each and every action, moment, emotion is so fantastically done that reader is engrossed in reading all the time. I finished this book in one go reading it overnight because I personally found it so engaging. Also it&apos;s a true stor</span>
  <span id="freeText5945465940433655492" style="display:none">This is the second book of Richard Bach which I read after Jonathan Livingston Seagull .<br />Richard has a flawless art of story telling. It engages the reader so well that reader itself feels as it's his own life-story being narrated. The eye towards details , capturing of each and every action, moment, emotion is so fantastically done that reader is engrossed in reading all the time. I finished this book in one go reading it overnight because I personally found it so engaging. Also it's a true story which beautifully explains meaning of Soul mate and how we humans are constantly engaged in finding that perfect one ... Also we consciously/unconsciously keep on making conversations with our future self but here its opposite ... The author has given a narrative of his past self i.e making a conversation with himself when he was a child , to his 9 year old self...<br />A good read for everyone who still look for a soul mate and the ones who have already found they will get a deeper understanding of it</span>
